HOUSE BILL 993
N1 6lr3136
HB 705/25 – ENT CF SB 666
By: Delegates Valderrama, Amprey, Bhandari, and Qi
Introduced and read first time: February 6, 2026
Assigned to: Economic Matters
Committee Report: Favorable
House action: Adopted with floor amendments
Read second time: March 4, 2026
CHAPTER ______
1 AN ACT concerning
2 Real Property – Short–Term Rentals
3 FOR the purpose of prohibiting the governing body of a county or municipality from
4 enacting a local law or ordinance prohibiting the offering of certain residential
5 property as a short–term rental by an operator solely because the operator is a lessee
6 or sublessee of the property; authorizing the governing body of a county or
7 municipality to enact a local law or ordinance prohibiting the operator of a
8 short–term rental who is a lessee or sublessee of the property from operating more
9 than one short–term rental within the county or municipality; and generally relating
10 to short–term rental property.
11 BY adding to
12 Article – Real Property
13 Section 14–126.1
14 Annotated Code of Maryland
15 (2023 Replacement Volume and 2025 Supplement)
16 SECTION 1. BE IT ENACTED BY THE GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF MARYLAND,
17 That the Laws of Maryland read as follows:
18 Article – Real Property
19 14–126.1.
EXPLANATION: CAPITALS INDICATE MATTER ADDED TO EXISTING LAW.
[Brackets] indicate matter deleted from existing law.
Underlining indicates amendments to bill.
Strike out indicates matter stricken from the bill by amendment or deleted from the law by
amendment. *hb0993*

2 HOUSE BILL 993
1 (A) (1) IN THIS SECTION THE FOLLOWING WORDS HAVE THE MEANINGS
2 INDICATED.
3 (2) “OPERATOR” MEANS THE PROPRIETOR OF ANY DWELLING,
4 LODGING, OR SLEEPING ACCOMMODATIONS OFFERED AS A SHORT–TERM RENTAL,
5 WHETHER IN THE CAPACITY OF OWNER, LESSEE, SUBLESSEE, MORTGAGEE IN
6 POSSESSION, LICENSEE, OR ANY OTHER POSSESSORY CAPACITY.
7 (3) (I) “SHORT–TERM RENTAL” MEANS A RESIDENTIAL DWELLING
8 UNIT OR A PORTION OF THE UNIT, INCLUDING AN ACCESSORY DWELLING, USED TO
9 PROVIDE HOUSING FOR LESS THAN 31 CONSECUTIVE DAYS.
10 (II) “SHORT–TERM RENTAL” DOES NOT INCLUDE A HOTEL OR
11 MOTEL, BOARDING HOUSE, GROUP RESIDENTIAL FACILITY FOR STUDENTS,
12 FRATERNITY OR SORORITY HOUSE, OR SIMILAR HOUSING.
13 (B) (1) THE GOVERNING BODY OF A COUNTY OR MUNICIPALITY MAY NOT
14 ENACT A LOCAL LAW OR ORDINANCE PROHIBITING AN OPERATOR FROM OFFERING
15 A PROPERTY AS A SHORT–TERM RENTAL SOLELY BECAUSE THE OPERATOR IS A
16 LESSEE OR SUBLESSEE OF THE PROPERTY.
17 (2) THE GOVERNING BODY OF A COUNTY OR MUNICIPALITY MAY
18 ENACT A LOCAL LAW OR ORDINANCE PROHIBITING AN OPERATOR FROM OPERATING
19 MORE THAN ONE PROPERTY IN THE COUNTY OR MUNICIPALITY AS A SHORT–TERM
20 RENTAL IF THE OPERATOR IS A LESSEE OR SUBLESSEE OF THE PROPERTY.
21 (C) NOTHING IN THIS SECTION MAY BE INTERPRETED AS PROHIBITING A;
22 (1) A PROPERTY OWNER FROM PROHIBITING OR LIMITING THE USE
23 OF THE PROPERTY BY A LESSEE OR SUBLESSEE AS A SHORT–TERM RENTAL; OR
24 (2) A COUNTY OR MUNICIPAL GOVERNMENT FROM REQUIRING AN
25 OPERATOR TO REGISTER A SHORT–TERM RENTAL.
26 SECTION 2. AND BE IT FURTHER ENACTED, That this Act shall take effect
27 October 1, 2026.

